WEBVTT

00:00.667 --> 00:03.795
(intriguing orchestral music)

00:06.089 --> 00:10.135
(slow acoustic guitar picking)

00:13.513 --> 00:14.264
(hooves clopping)

00:14.305 --> 00:17.559
(horses whinnying)

00:53.428 --> 00:55.930
(upbeat music)

01:02.020 --> 01:04.105
(elevator dings)

01:04.105 --> 01:04.898
- Here you go Alex.

01:04.939 --> 01:06.107
- Good morning, Carla.

01:06.149 --> 01:07.275
- Roger wants tosee you by 2 p.m.

01:07.275 --> 01:08.109
- Did he say why?

01:08.151 --> 01:09.486
- No, just for you to stop by.

01:09.527 --> 01:10.570
- Interesting, thanks.

01:10.612 --> 01:11.780
- Good morning, Stan.

01:11.780 --> 01:12.655
Those new aerowheels look great.

01:12.697 --> 01:14.240
- Thanks!

01:14.282 --> 01:16.034
- The new SF-15s came in.

01:16.075 --> 01:17.786
- Adjusted bindings?- Yeah, per your specs.

01:17.786 --> 01:19.454
- Wanna take it out on afield test this weekend?

01:19.454 --> 01:20.789
- Absolutely.- Have fun.

01:20.789 --> 01:22.290
- Why don't you do it, Alex?

01:22.332 --> 01:23.625
I can't remember the lasttime you did a field test.

01:23.666 --> 01:25.502
Have you ever done a field test?

01:25.543 --> 01:26.961
- Good morning, Ben.

01:27.003 --> 01:28.129
Oh, those are fantastic.

01:28.171 --> 01:29.380
I'm gonna need a newvendor report on those

01:29.422 --> 01:30.507
by Monday, though.- Will do.

01:30.548 --> 01:31.633
- I saw you finally gotthe kinks out of the

01:31.633 --> 01:33.259
Kaza Insta-Cabin.- Yes, we did.

01:33.301 --> 01:36.012
Thank you so much for yourconcern about our new products.

01:36.054 --> 01:37.347
Morning, Phil.- Hey!

01:37.388 --> 01:38.723
- I like to keep up with what'shappening with new vendors.

01:38.765 --> 01:41.142
It's all part ofbeing a good VP.

01:41.184 --> 01:42.227
- But you're not a VP.

01:42.268 --> 01:43.561
- Well, not yet.

01:46.648 --> 01:47.816
- You're a director,just like me.

01:47.816 --> 01:49.567
- But I have plans.

01:49.609 --> 01:51.319
- There still needsto be a job opening.

01:51.319 --> 01:52.737
- You haven't heard.- Heard what?

01:52.779 --> 01:53.738
- Hey Alex!

01:53.780 --> 01:55.198
Ben!

01:55.240 --> 01:56.199
- Hello Roger!

01:56.241 --> 01:57.492
- Lookin' good Roger!

01:57.534 --> 01:59.410
- Hey Alex, I know we'resupposed to meet later,

01:59.452 --> 02:01.037
but grab a helmet and join me.

02:01.079 --> 02:01.996
It'll be fun!

02:02.997 --> 02:05.083
- Oh, I have a 9:30call with Oslo.

02:05.125 --> 02:07.168
We're onboarding anew ski vendor, so.

02:07.210 --> 02:08.503
- That's fantastic news!

02:08.503 --> 02:11.214
- It is fantastic news,especially since I just found a

02:11.256 --> 02:13.258
place where we candistribute our new gear.

02:13.299 --> 02:14.175
- You did?

02:15.844 --> 02:17.053
- Where?

02:17.095 --> 02:18.221
- Hackett, Arizona.

02:18.263 --> 02:20.431
Former tire factory,perfect for the

02:20.473 --> 02:22.141
distribution center you wanted.

02:22.183 --> 02:23.768
- What about itsenvironmental compliance?

02:23.810 --> 02:25.186
- They're already up on all the

02:25.186 --> 02:26.729
Green Building CouncilStandards, with just the bare

02:26.771 --> 02:29.607
minimum for us to get itin shape for our usage.

02:30.567 --> 02:31.860
- Well, all righty.

02:31.901 --> 02:33.987
Grab a helmet Ben,and tell me more.

02:34.028 --> 02:35.113
- On my way!

02:35.155 --> 02:36.406
Told you I had plans.

02:38.700 --> 02:41.452
(Roger chuckles)

02:43.830 --> 02:45.582
- It's my fault, Ishould've just gone up

02:45.623 --> 02:46.916
when Roger asked me to.

02:46.958 --> 02:47.876
- Why didn't you?

02:47.876 --> 02:49.502
- You know I don't rock climb.

02:49.544 --> 02:51.045
Kayak...

02:51.045 --> 02:51.880
Or ski...

02:51.921 --> 02:52.881
Camp.

02:52.881 --> 02:54.340
- And yet?- And yet,

02:54.382 --> 02:55.884
how do you say no toa job at the biggest

02:55.884 --> 02:58.177
outdoor recreationalgoods retailer?

02:58.219 --> 03:00.013
- You don't.- Exactly.

03:00.054 --> 03:01.723
I mean, the company'sreputation is the reason why

03:01.764 --> 03:03.725
I agreed to be recruited.

03:03.766 --> 03:07.979
Even if outdoorsy isn'texactly my natural orientation.

03:09.397 --> 03:11.065
- Executive Assistantgrapevine says

03:11.065 --> 03:13.568
Tom Davis is staying inSpain after his honeymoon,

03:13.568 --> 03:15.486
which means--- A VP spot is opening up.

03:15.528 --> 03:17.113
- Mm-hmm.- Ben's gonna go hard

03:17.155 --> 03:19.490
for that spot, andhe has seniority.

03:19.532 --> 03:20.575
- Well, he may have only been at

03:20.575 --> 03:22.035
Great Frontiers for a year--

03:22.076 --> 03:24.579
- And a half--- But, Roger respects you.

03:24.579 --> 03:27.415
Maybe that's why Roger wantsto talk with you later.

03:27.415 --> 03:29.500
- I hadn't thought about that.

03:29.542 --> 03:30.835
But Ben's alreadygot a lead on Roger's

03:30.877 --> 03:33.046
new distribution center, so--- So?

03:33.087 --> 03:35.298
Find something elseto take the lead on.

03:42.972 --> 03:45.767
(upbeat music)

03:47.602 --> 03:50.855
(horses whinnying)

03:55.693 --> 03:58.029
(laughing)

04:00.365 --> 04:03.117
(loud hammering)

04:09.582 --> 04:10.667
- All right.

04:16.965 --> 04:17.966
All right.

04:20.218 --> 04:23.012
Young man, a little mementofrom your stay with us.

04:23.054 --> 04:24.514
Thank you so much.

04:27.684 --> 04:28.643
All right, all for you.

04:28.643 --> 04:29.519
High five.

04:30.645 --> 04:31.813
Five!

04:31.813 --> 04:33.815
All right.- Thank you so much, Josh.

04:33.856 --> 04:35.525
- You're welcome.

04:37.860 --> 04:39.362
Michael!- Hey, how are you?

04:39.404 --> 04:40.655
- Good to have you back.- Yeah, great to be back.

04:40.655 --> 04:41.656
- How are you?- Good, good, good.

04:41.698 --> 04:42.991
- Good.- Yeah, I left the office

04:43.032 --> 04:44.784
and went straightto Fresno Airport.

04:44.826 --> 04:47.203
You know I'm not gonnamiss the Centennial, now.

04:47.245 --> 04:48.288
- Would not have beenthe same without you.

04:48.329 --> 04:50.164
Checked in?- No, no.

04:50.206 --> 04:51.082
I'm gonna go do it right now.

04:51.124 --> 04:52.333
- Get checked in, come meet me.

04:52.375 --> 04:55.086
- Okay, see you later.- All right, see you.

04:59.549 --> 05:01.092
- There you go.- Okay.

05:03.177 --> 05:04.929
- Hi, hello, how are you?

05:06.264 --> 05:08.683
Is that Serena Monroe'scar I saw leaving?

05:08.725 --> 05:10.518
- It was.- It was, okay.

05:11.561 --> 05:13.354
Did she make us an offer?- She did.

05:13.396 --> 05:17.191
- Good, I'll file it away inmy special filing cabinet.

05:20.945 --> 05:24.991
- That is why I do the filing.

05:26.784 --> 05:28.953
(sighs) It's a good offer, Josh.

05:30.038 --> 05:31.581
- A good offer in theory.

05:31.622 --> 05:33.416
I don't need to read thatcontract from that ranch

05:33.458 --> 05:35.460
to know that they just wannalevel this place for pasture.

05:35.501 --> 05:38.504
- And if the banks cared aboutkeeping this place intact,

05:38.546 --> 05:40.381
we wouldn't be where we are.

05:41.716 --> 05:44.719
But numbers with deadlinesare all banks care about.

05:44.719 --> 05:46.888
And we need tostart caring, too,

05:46.888 --> 05:48.514
while we still havea say in the matter,

05:48.556 --> 05:50.725
which we won't bythe end of the month.

05:50.725 --> 05:54.145
- Centennial is in a week.- I know.

05:54.187 --> 05:56.439
And Serena says shewants an answer by then.

05:56.481 --> 05:59.067
She knows exactly when thebanks will come calling.

05:59.108 --> 06:01.027
- And Dad would be really upset.

06:01.069 --> 06:04.030
If he knew we were thinkingabout selling this place.

06:04.072 --> 06:05.907
- But Dad didn'twanna turn Harmony

06:05.907 --> 06:08.534
into a dude ranch, either.

06:08.576 --> 06:09.577
But we did.

06:09.577 --> 06:10.453
We had to.

06:11.537 --> 06:13.331
And it almost worked.

06:16.918 --> 06:17.752
- Almost.

06:18.753 --> 06:21.089
(soft music)

06:24.759 --> 06:26.886
- Hi, Grace said I should just--

06:26.928 --> 06:28.429
- Yes, here.

06:28.471 --> 06:29.347
Try this.

06:31.516 --> 06:33.226
Potential vendor.- Okay.

06:36.229 --> 06:37.063
Oh.

06:41.692 --> 06:44.028
What is it supposed to be?- In theory,

06:44.070 --> 06:45.613
freeze-dried lasagna.

06:46.697 --> 06:47.782
- Takes like oatmeal.

06:47.782 --> 06:49.951
- I'll put that down as a pass.

06:49.951 --> 06:52.328
But that is not why you're here.

06:53.704 --> 06:56.624
I think...

06:56.666 --> 06:58.584
I think a change is in order.

06:58.626 --> 06:59.460
- Regarding?

07:00.211 --> 07:02.004
- The Great Frontiers retreat.

07:03.256 --> 07:05.133
- Retreat?- Retreat.

07:05.174 --> 07:08.219
As you know, every yearwe pick someplace new.

07:08.261 --> 07:09.762
Maui, Yosemite, Grand Cayman.

07:09.804 --> 07:10.847
That was nice.

07:10.888 --> 07:13.516
But I have a new idea.

07:15.810 --> 07:17.937
Harmony Dude Ranchin North Dakota.

07:18.771 --> 07:20.398
- Dude?- Ranch.

07:21.482 --> 07:23.526
I've always had a softspot for the Old West.

07:23.568 --> 07:24.819
This one's new on the market.

07:24.819 --> 07:26.737
700 acres, owned bya brother and sister,

07:26.779 --> 07:28.698
Josh and Taylor Ketchum.- Hold on,

07:28.739 --> 07:31.159
you're thinking about buying?- I am.

07:31.159 --> 07:32.326
That's the new idea.

07:33.494 --> 07:34.829
- Only for a retreat.

07:35.705 --> 07:37.123
- You have another suggestion?

07:37.165 --> 07:38.875
- Well, it's justcompany-wide we only

07:38.916 --> 07:40.960
have a few retreats every year.

07:41.002 --> 07:41.878
- That's true.

07:43.671 --> 07:46.132
- Wait, what about, what ifwe used it as something else

07:46.174 --> 07:47.091
for the rest of the time?

07:47.133 --> 07:48.593
Like an employeetraining center.

07:48.634 --> 07:50.678
I mean, we're growingout of the one in Denver.

07:50.678 --> 07:51.846
- I like where you're going.

07:51.846 --> 07:53.806
- I mean, we could evendo our bootcamps there.

07:53.848 --> 07:54.724
- Yes.

07:54.765 --> 07:56.017
Oh, that's perfect!

07:56.809 --> 07:58.311
Why don't you goand scout the place

07:58.352 --> 07:59.937
and see if it's up toGreat Frontiers standards?

07:59.979 --> 08:01.939
- You want me to scout--- I know, I know.

08:01.981 --> 08:03.524
Normally Ben goes, but he's off

08:03.566 --> 08:05.693
to Arizona scouting thepotential distribution center.

08:05.693 --> 08:06.986
- Right, it's just--- Should only

08:07.028 --> 08:08.321
take a couple of days.

08:08.362 --> 08:09.822
But it has to be ASAP.

08:09.864 --> 08:11.949
My agent tells me there'sanother offer on the place.

08:11.991 --> 08:13.201
- But I--- Look,

08:13.201 --> 08:15.119
if Harmony isn'tright we'll pass.

08:16.329 --> 08:21.000
By then, Ben should be backand he can take it from here.

08:21.042 --> 08:21.918
What do you say?

08:25.004 --> 08:27.590
(upbeat music)

08:44.065 --> 08:46.234
- Reception's a bitspotty out here.

08:49.904 --> 08:51.822
Harmony Ranch is just up ahead.

08:51.864 --> 08:52.949
- Thank you.

09:15.263 --> 09:16.514
- Reins.

09:16.556 --> 09:20.059
Gotta keep 'em closer to you.- Like that?

09:47.962 --> 09:50.965
(horses whinnying)

09:51.966 --> 09:55.094
(camera shuttering)

10:05.187 --> 10:08.107
(horse snuffling)

10:24.665 --> 10:27.752
(guests chattering)

10:29.670 --> 10:32.965
- Welcome to Harmony!- Hi, I'm a late arrival.

10:33.007 --> 10:35.009
- Ms. McKenna fromGreat Frontiers?

10:35.051 --> 10:36.052
- Yes.

10:36.093 --> 10:37.261
Please, call me Alex.

10:38.179 --> 10:39.930
You must be one of the Ketchums.

10:39.972 --> 10:41.182
- Sure am.

10:41.182 --> 10:42.016
Taylor Ketchum,nice to meet you.

10:42.058 --> 10:43.100
- Nice to meet you.

10:43.142 --> 10:45.353
This place is amazing.- Thanks.

10:45.394 --> 10:47.855
I grew up here so it's kindahard to have perspective.

10:47.897 --> 10:49.190
- I know exactly what you mean.

10:49.190 --> 10:50.566
I grew up in suburban Ohio.

10:50.608 --> 10:52.526
I didn't realize howbeautiful it was until I left.

10:52.526 --> 10:54.695
- Oh, well I'll have totake your word for it.

10:54.695 --> 10:56.364
The leaving andcoming back part.

10:56.405 --> 10:57.573
I've never been to Ohio.

10:57.615 --> 10:59.116
I mean, I've neverbeen anywhere, really.

10:59.158 --> 11:01.202
I would like to go places.

11:01.243 --> 11:02.620
(laughing)

11:02.662 --> 11:04.538
Okay, let's get you situated.

11:05.539 --> 11:06.457
- Okay.

11:06.499 --> 11:09.085
(upbeat music)

11:10.169 --> 11:11.837
- All right.

11:11.879 --> 11:12.713
Thanks.

11:13.839 --> 11:14.715
- Hey, Josh.

11:15.966 --> 11:20.471
I kinda overslept and missedthe lasso lesson this morning.

11:20.513 --> 11:22.098
- How long you been coming here?

11:22.139 --> 11:23.933
- I don't know, five years, why?

11:23.974 --> 11:26.185
- You should know it's alariat, it's not a lasso.

11:26.227 --> 11:28.479
- Right, right.- So.

11:28.521 --> 11:32.149
- How 'bout now?- Yeah, now's fine.

11:32.191 --> 11:33.234
Let's go.- Okay.

11:35.027 --> 11:36.404
- I can't believe you guysare selling the ranch.

11:36.404 --> 11:38.364
It seems so popular.

11:38.406 --> 11:39.990
- Yeah, this week, sure.

11:40.032 --> 11:42.993
But that's because of ourCentennial celebration.

11:43.035 --> 11:44.578
A lot of our regularguests are back,

11:44.578 --> 11:45.955
so we're busier than usual.

11:45.996 --> 11:47.873
But catch us most any other time

11:47.915 --> 11:51.168
and there are halfas many folks here.

11:51.210 --> 11:53.045
- So beautiful.- Thanks,

11:53.087 --> 11:56.173
but we got a late start inthe dude ranch business.

11:56.215 --> 11:59.176
We were still a working ranchonly until six years ago.

11:59.218 --> 12:00.511
- What made you change it?

12:01.512 --> 12:04.014
- Our dad passed away.- Oh, I'm so sorry.

12:04.056 --> 12:05.433
- Thank you.

12:05.474 --> 12:08.436
Dad thought dude rancheswere basically resorts.

12:08.477 --> 12:10.104
And he wasn't wrong.

12:10.104 --> 12:13.315
But maybe if we'd gonethat route earlier.

12:16.652 --> 12:20.489
I know you're just taking alook around for your boss,

12:20.531 --> 12:23.451
but if you don't mind,I'd appreciate it if you'd

12:23.451 --> 12:26.120
keep the fact we're sellingto yourself, at this point.

12:26.120 --> 12:28.831
I don't wanna upsetany longtime guests.

12:28.873 --> 12:30.416
- My lips are sealed.

12:30.458 --> 12:32.918
- Wow, is this my cabin?- It is.

12:32.960 --> 12:36.547
Well, yours and Jill's.- Jill?

12:36.589 --> 12:38.758
(laughing)

12:38.799 --> 12:40.009
- Jill Tanner from Modesto.

12:40.050 --> 12:43.137
Nice to meet you, Alex.- And you are my--

12:43.179 --> 12:45.306
- Cabinmate for a couple days.

12:45.306 --> 12:46.390
- Oh.

12:46.432 --> 12:47.683
I just thought that--- Your reservation

12:47.725 --> 12:49.810
came so last secondthat we had to bunk up.

12:49.810 --> 12:51.854
Mr. Hilton's officesaid it would be okay

12:51.896 --> 12:53.939
since you were only gonna behere 'til day after tomorrow.

12:53.981 --> 12:56.358
- That is true.- And the only other option

12:56.400 --> 12:58.068
was the ranch hand bunk house.

12:58.110 --> 13:00.738
- Oh, well, we'll befine, this is great.

13:00.779 --> 13:01.864
- Okay.

13:01.906 --> 13:03.157
I have to head backto the front desk,

13:03.282 --> 13:05.075
and I have to start preppingthe coals for dinner.

13:05.117 --> 13:07.077
- Taylor's barbecue is the best.

13:07.119 --> 13:08.788
- And my pumpkincheesecake's even better.

13:08.829 --> 13:09.830
- Mm, accurate.

13:12.208 --> 13:13.083
Don't fret.

13:13.125 --> 13:15.002
I promise, I'm great at sharing.

13:15.002 --> 13:17.296
You can ask my ex-husband.- Oh.

13:17.338 --> 13:18.005
- Gary.

13:18.047 --> 13:19.089
It's all amicable.

13:19.131 --> 13:20.382
I'm the kinda personwho always wanted

13:20.424 --> 13:21.842
to go outdoors andfind adventures,

13:21.842 --> 13:23.302
and he's more ofa watch adventures

13:23.344 --> 13:24.678
from a distance kind of guy.

13:24.678 --> 13:26.138
So now I can come toplaces like Harmony

13:26.180 --> 13:28.349
for a fresh startand meet new people.

13:28.349 --> 13:29.350
Like you.

13:29.391 --> 13:30.684
Look at me, oversharing.

13:30.726 --> 13:33.229
(laughing)- Okay then.

13:33.270 --> 13:35.022
- Come on, let meshow you your room.

13:35.064 --> 13:36.565
- Ooh, wait, okay.

13:37.650 --> 13:40.110
(lasso whipping)

13:40.152 --> 13:42.279
- All right?- Okay.

13:42.321 --> 13:43.697
I think.

13:43.739 --> 13:44.865
- Now, you got this.

14:10.099 --> 14:12.977
(cat meowing)

14:13.018 --> 14:18.107
- There you go.

14:20.609 --> 14:23.153
- And then when youget really good,

14:23.195 --> 14:25.072
you can start doing this stuff.

14:26.198 --> 14:26.949
- [Alex] What?

14:26.991 --> 14:27.825
(Alex squealing)

14:27.866 --> 14:30.452
- Whoa, Josh.- I am so sorry.

14:30.494 --> 14:32.204
Oh, I'm sorry.

14:33.247 --> 14:34.915
- Most guys justask for my number.

14:37.251 --> 14:38.961
- You all right?- Yeah.

14:41.255 --> 14:43.424
This is what we calla funny story one day.

14:43.424 --> 14:44.633
(laughing)

14:44.675 --> 14:45.759
- Let's start over.

14:45.801 --> 14:47.595
Josh Ketchum,co-owner of Harmony.

14:47.636 --> 14:48.888
- Alex McKenna.- Nice to meet you.

14:48.929 --> 14:52.433
This is my guest.- Nice to meet you.

14:52.433 --> 14:54.268
- Nice to meet you.

14:54.268 --> 14:55.311
- McKenna, I don't--

14:55.352 --> 14:56.604
- I just got here.

14:56.604 --> 14:58.105
Late arrival.

14:58.147 --> 15:00.107
- Yeah, no, I get all the names,

15:00.149 --> 15:02.860
I just don't recognize that one.

15:02.902 --> 15:03.736
- Oh.

15:06.363 --> 15:07.239
- Welcome.

15:08.449 --> 15:09.825
- Don't get mad.

15:09.867 --> 15:11.201
- Well, that's practically aguarantee he's gonna get mad.

15:11.243 --> 15:12.161
- Why am I getting mad?

15:12.202 --> 15:15.039
- See?- Nothing's official.

15:16.707 --> 15:17.625
- Are you a lawyer or something?

15:17.666 --> 15:18.626
- Definitely not.

15:19.627 --> 15:21.003
- Okay, then whatbrings you here?

15:21.045 --> 15:24.006
- It's the ranch.- To scout and possibly buy.

15:24.840 --> 15:26.091
- Are you from Monroe?

15:26.133 --> 15:27.468
Because Monroe knows whatthis property looks like.

15:27.468 --> 15:28.886
- I'm sorry, what's Monroe?

15:28.927 --> 15:31.138
- Alex is from Great Frontiers.

15:32.389 --> 15:33.432
- I don't know that ranch.

15:33.474 --> 15:34.808
- No, it's not a ranch.

15:34.850 --> 15:36.644
We're the leading onlineretailers of sportswear,

15:36.644 --> 15:39.104
camping gear,mountaineering equipment.

15:39.146 --> 15:40.189
Really never heard of us?

15:40.314 --> 15:42.816
- Do you sell cowboy boots?- Actually, no.

15:44.151 --> 15:45.277
- Then no.

15:45.319 --> 15:47.363
So you'll understand thatI don't understand why

15:47.404 --> 15:48.822
you'd want to buy this place.

15:48.864 --> 15:50.240
