32:25.360 --> 32:26.486
- What agreement?

32:26.486 --> 32:28.863
You're out there toscout, not make deals.

32:28.905 --> 32:29.989
- I know.

32:30.031 --> 32:31.157
It's just, if we want achance to make a deal,

32:31.157 --> 32:33.618
then we have toget them to let us

32:33.660 --> 32:34.827
be the ones who buy it.

32:34.827 --> 32:36.996
- So there is another buyer?

32:37.038 --> 32:39.248
- Yeah, it's a big ranch.

32:39.290 --> 32:40.583
They wanna swallow Harmony up.

32:40.625 --> 32:43.836
But Josh does not want that.- Ah ha.

32:43.878 --> 32:45.630
And what does Josh want?

32:47.006 --> 32:48.716
- To keep his family'sranch the way it's been

32:48.758 --> 32:50.176
for the past 100 years.

32:50.176 --> 32:52.345
If we can convincehim we'll do that,

32:52.387 --> 32:54.347
I think we'll beatout the other buyer.

32:54.389 --> 32:55.640
(blender rumbling)

32:55.682 --> 32:57.225
He wants to show me thefiner points of ranch life

32:57.266 --> 33:00.061
so I'll better appreciatewhat this place has to offer.

33:00.103 --> 33:01.354
- Really?

33:01.396 --> 33:03.231
Are you okay with that?- Absolutely.

33:03.272 --> 33:06.984
It's been interesting so far.

33:07.026 --> 33:08.695
But I need to staythrough until Saturday.

33:08.695 --> 33:10.989
They're having aCentennial celebration.

33:11.030 --> 33:12.281
- Celebration?

33:12.323 --> 33:13.408
I love a celebration.

33:15.952 --> 33:18.079
- Do I have your okay then?- You do.

33:18.121 --> 33:21.416
Just be back in the officeby Monday with a full report.

33:21.457 --> 33:23.292
- Okay.- Oh, and Alex.

33:23.334 --> 33:25.962
Don't make any promisesto the Ketchums.

33:27.338 --> 33:28.214
- I got it.

33:30.925 --> 33:34.387
- Smoothie?- No, I'm good.

33:34.387 --> 33:36.931
You ready to talk about this?- Let's do it.

33:54.615 --> 33:57.410
(upbeat music)

34:08.546 --> 34:11.090
- [Josh] So you were sent hereto scout, not make an offer?

34:11.132 --> 34:12.300
- [Alex] That's right.

34:13.384 --> 34:14.802
- It seems like youwanna buy this place.

34:14.844 --> 34:17.096
Why would you bedoing all this stuff?

34:18.431 --> 34:19.515
- It's a long story.

34:20.475 --> 34:22.310
- Well, good thing we have time.

34:22.351 --> 34:25.396
And you wanna massage itall the way to the seam.

34:25.438 --> 34:26.314
- Oh.- Yeah.

34:27.273 --> 34:29.358
- There's a VP position opening.

34:29.400 --> 34:31.819
I'm in competitionwith someone for it.

34:31.861 --> 34:33.321
He's bringing in a big deal,

34:33.362 --> 34:35.740
so I need to bring onein, too, if I want a shot.

34:38.367 --> 34:40.203
- So it's just business.

34:41.704 --> 34:44.165
- You say that likeit's a bad thing.

34:44.207 --> 34:45.875
- It is, if it's the only thing.

34:46.793 --> 34:48.294
- Oh, come on,you're one to talk.

34:48.336 --> 34:50.797
Your entire life is aboutthe business of this ranch.

34:50.838 --> 34:54.509
- Now, how would you knowwhat my whole life's about?

34:54.550 --> 34:55.593
- Okay, fine.

34:56.677 --> 34:59.472
Tell me one of your interestsoutside of ranching.

35:01.099 --> 35:03.643
And don't say football,'cause all guys say football.

35:05.019 --> 35:06.604
- Hmm.- Mm-hmm.

35:09.440 --> 35:10.274
- Stars.

35:12.151 --> 35:14.445
I can name every singlemajor constellation

35:14.487 --> 35:16.322
in the northern hemisphere.- Wow.

35:18.950 --> 35:20.284
Hmm.

35:20.326 --> 35:23.496
Well, I guess, I guess NorthDakota's probably pretty good

35:23.496 --> 35:27.416
for that kind of thing.- It is one of the best.

35:27.458 --> 35:28.417
You tried it?

35:28.459 --> 35:30.670
- I haven't had a chance yet.

35:30.711 --> 35:32.839
Fell asleep superearly last night.

35:32.880 --> 35:34.507
It's funny, usuallyI am up all night

35:34.507 --> 35:36.509
on my phone answeringa million emails.

35:36.509 --> 35:39.846
But I can't do that here.- Perfect.

35:39.846 --> 35:41.472
Lose the phone.

35:41.514 --> 35:43.015
Embrace the nighttime sky.

35:44.308 --> 35:45.643
The moon's almost full, sothe stars aren't as bright,

35:45.685 --> 35:48.437
but it's amazing.

35:49.730 --> 35:51.816
- I just might do that.- You should.

35:56.529 --> 36:00.783
Okay, so outside of work, whatare some of your interests?

36:00.825 --> 36:01.701
- Football.

36:03.536 --> 36:06.205
(laughing)

36:06.205 --> 36:08.457
(upbeat music)

36:08.499 --> 36:09.625
- Woo!- Oh!

36:10.501 --> 36:13.170
Oh!- Oh, man!

36:13.212 --> 36:16.424
- Are you okay?- Yeah, I'm fine.

36:16.465 --> 36:18.426
I'm telling you, thatrock came out of nowhere.

36:18.467 --> 36:19.802
- They're knownfor their stealth.

36:19.844 --> 36:21.971
- Oh!- That's impressive.

36:23.222 --> 36:25.057
You managed to hit the onespot that wasn't protected.

36:25.057 --> 36:26.559
- Yeah, it's okay.

36:26.601 --> 36:27.810
It's just nothing.- Mm.

36:27.852 --> 36:29.228
- Yeah, it's just myshoulder, it's good, yeah.

36:29.270 --> 36:31.272
- Hold on, strong man.

36:31.314 --> 36:34.192
Just until we getback to the ranch.

36:34.233 --> 36:35.401
- All right, whoa.- You can ride

36:35.401 --> 36:36.652
with one arm.- What are you?

36:36.694 --> 36:38.905
Some kind of fielddoctor or something?

36:38.946 --> 36:40.072
(laughing)

36:40.072 --> 36:43.201
- Well, I'm a mom,so same thing.

36:43.242 --> 36:45.536
- So, how are the twins?

36:45.578 --> 36:47.288
- They just startedmiddle school.

36:47.330 --> 36:48.414
- Really?- Mm-hmm.

36:48.456 --> 36:51.083
- Gary has them this week, so--

36:51.125 --> 36:54.462
- Are you okay with all that?- Oh, great.

36:54.503 --> 36:56.464
Gary's great, I'm great.

36:56.505 --> 36:59.592
We just ultimatelyweren't great together.

36:59.592 --> 37:00.593
- Hm.- It happens.

37:00.593 --> 37:02.428
- I see.- What about you?

37:02.470 --> 37:05.514
Are you dating?- Not since Susie.

37:05.556 --> 37:07.600
Do you remember her?- Is she the one who

37:07.600 --> 37:09.393
brought her dinner tothe Christmas party?

37:09.435 --> 37:11.979
- Yeah, yeah she wasalways really particular

37:12.021 --> 37:13.147
about her food.

37:13.189 --> 37:16.776
But we broke up not longafter I got my new job.

37:16.776 --> 37:19.570
- No one since?- Not yet.

37:19.612 --> 37:22.698
I mean, this time, I'mshooting for amazing.

37:25.284 --> 37:27.495
- Well, who knows?

37:27.536 --> 37:28.955
Maybe she'll come out of nowhere

37:28.955 --> 37:30.456
when you least expect it.

37:31.749 --> 37:32.875
Like a rock.

37:37.672 --> 37:39.632
- Right, but how areyou not a Seahawks fan?

37:39.674 --> 37:40.967
- Because I grew up in Ohio,

37:40.967 --> 37:42.510
and you pick you teamwhen you're little

37:42.551 --> 37:43.844
and you stick with it forthe rest of your life,

37:43.886 --> 37:45.054
no matter what.

37:45.096 --> 37:47.014
Those are the rules,don't ask me why.

37:47.056 --> 37:48.641
Believe me, there aretimes every season

37:48.683 --> 37:53.145
I wish I was born in Boston.- Oh, no thanks.

37:53.187 --> 37:54.814
This is GiGi.- GiGi?

37:56.148 --> 37:57.733
- Yeah, this is oneof Taylor's horses.

37:58.609 --> 38:00.111
- She's a beauty.

38:00.152 --> 38:01.946
Hi.- You've ever ridden a horse?

38:03.614 --> 38:04.907
- Used to be my whole life.

38:07.660 --> 38:08.744
- Horses?

38:10.621 --> 38:11.455
- Yeah.

38:12.832 --> 38:13.833
- Really?

38:13.874 --> 38:15.960
- Yeah, I rode dressagefor five years,

38:16.002 --> 38:18.546
up until I turned 15.- Wow.

38:20.631 --> 38:22.717
What made you quit?- Money.

38:23.676 --> 38:25.761
- Yeah, money.

38:25.803 --> 38:26.887
- My mom sold insurance,

38:26.929 --> 38:29.348
my dad was a highschool science teacher.

38:29.390 --> 38:30.725
They both knew howmuch it meant to me,

38:30.766 --> 38:33.769
so they worked extra so I couldkeep riding and competing.

38:35.146 --> 38:38.399
When I realized how hardit was on them, I quit.

38:41.027 --> 38:42.111
- Really?

38:42.153 --> 38:43.696
Just like that.- Probably counts as

38:43.696 --> 38:44.822
my first heartbreak.

38:46.615 --> 38:49.160
- You ridden since?- No.

38:52.121 --> 38:53.706
- Maybe we should change that.

38:59.045 --> 39:00.629
- Yeah?- Yeah.

39:00.671 --> 39:03.007
(soft music)

39:23.069 --> 39:25.863
(upbeat music)

39:57.645 --> 39:59.814
(laughing)

40:02.900 --> 40:05.402
- Man, I am impressed.

40:07.571 --> 40:08.697
Now we just needto get you a hat.

40:08.739 --> 40:09.907
(laughing)

40:09.949 --> 40:11.200
- Why, do you have anyin the lost and found,

40:11.242 --> 40:12.785
'cause I'm almost aspicky about my head wear

40:12.785 --> 40:16.247
as I am about my coffee.- Lost and found, huh?

40:16.288 --> 40:17.289
- (laughing) Hey.

40:17.289 --> 40:18.457
- I knew I recognizedthose boots.

40:19.291 --> 40:20.709
Hey, I'm about to go into town

40:20.751 --> 40:22.086
to get some suppliesfor the Centennial.

40:22.169 --> 40:25.005
Do you want to come with andpick up some new clothes?

40:25.840 --> 40:27.633
- I would love that.- Great.

40:27.633 --> 40:28.509
- Bye.

40:34.056 --> 40:36.976
- We like her?(horse snorting)

40:37.017 --> 40:38.352
Yeah, I think so, too.

40:39.812 --> 40:42.314
(upbeat music)

40:47.403 --> 40:49.947
(slow music)

40:59.373 --> 41:02.501
(upbeat music)

41:02.501 --> 41:05.087
(car rumbling)

41:06.672 --> 41:09.008
- You know, I can'thelp but noticing,

41:09.008 --> 41:12.469
as resistant as Josh is tothe idea of selling the ranch,

41:12.511 --> 41:14.972
you don't seem quiteso upset about it.

41:15.014 --> 41:17.516
- Don't get me wrong,I love the ranch.

41:17.516 --> 41:20.811
This whole place, I meanmy heritage is here.

41:20.853 --> 41:22.938
I even convinced Joshto build a little museum

41:22.980 --> 41:24.690
to the history of Harmony.

41:26.525 --> 41:27.359
- But?

41:28.819 --> 41:30.905
- But the world is a lotbigger than one ranch,

41:30.946 --> 41:32.114
and I wanna see it.

41:32.156 --> 41:33.949
I have friends fromhigh school already

41:33.991 --> 41:35.618
on their third passport.

41:35.659 --> 41:39.538
And here I am, buildingbarbecues and making pies.

41:39.538 --> 41:41.290
All of which are good, trust me.

41:46.670 --> 41:47.796
(bell chiming)

41:47.838 --> 41:50.049
Okay, clothes are inhere, food is at the back.

41:50.049 --> 41:51.300
So I'm gonna gather my supplies,

41:51.342 --> 41:53.761
and then we can meetback here at the bait.

41:53.802 --> 41:54.720
- The bait.

42:02.061 --> 42:03.145
Hmm.

42:10.110 --> 42:12.488
(laughing)

42:22.915 --> 42:23.999
Taylor?

42:25.417 --> 42:28.337
(Taylor shushing)

42:30.547 --> 42:31.382
What?

42:32.925 --> 42:33.801
What?

42:38.889 --> 42:41.934
Who is that?- Serena Monroe.

42:41.934 --> 42:44.186
- Monroe, as in Monroe Ranch?

42:44.228 --> 42:45.771
- She's gonna push mefor an answer about

42:45.771 --> 42:47.898
buying the ranch, andwe don't have one yet.

42:47.940 --> 42:49.108
- Okay, well, thendefinitely stay back.

42:49.149 --> 42:50.192
- Okay.

42:52.570 --> 42:54.029
- [Serena] Thanks so much.

42:54.989 --> 42:56.865
- Okay, she's gone, you're good.

42:59.201 --> 43:01.787
- Serena's always been alittle intimidating for me.

43:01.829 --> 43:03.205
I was even nervous around her

43:03.247 --> 43:05.124
when she and Josh used to date.

43:07.793 --> 43:10.629
- Wait, so Serenaand Josh used--

43:10.671 --> 43:11.880
- Oh, yeah.

43:11.964 --> 43:14.216
But that was before he wentto college and met Claire.

43:14.258 --> 43:16.969
She was the one whobroke his heart.

43:16.969 --> 43:18.512
- Claire?- Mm-hmm.

43:18.554 --> 43:20.889
She was his fiance fortwo years in grad school,

43:20.931 --> 43:23.934
and then one day hecame home from Ithaca

43:23.976 --> 43:25.019
and they weren'tengaged anymore,

43:25.060 --> 43:26.061
and he never talked about it,

43:26.103 --> 43:28.147
but I could tellit bothered him.

43:28.188 --> 43:30.316
- Wait, you don't thinkSerena trying to buy the ranch

43:30.316 --> 43:32.693
is personal, do you?- No, it's just good business.

43:32.735 --> 43:33.861
And if there's anything that

43:33.902 --> 43:36.030
Serena's all about,it's business.

43:36.071 --> 43:37.823
(bell chiming)

43:37.823 --> 43:40.034
Actually, Clairewas like that, too.

43:42.578 --> 43:45.080
Huh, I guess Josh has a type.

43:47.166 --> 43:49.752
And that's me totallyoversharing about my brother.

43:49.793 --> 43:51.837
(laughing)

43:51.879 --> 43:52.671
- Okay.

43:52.671 --> 43:55.049
(laughing)

43:56.842 --> 43:59.345
(upbeat music)

44:05.017 --> 44:06.352
(loud knocking)

44:06.393 --> 44:08.354
- Am I interrupting?- Ben, perfect.

44:08.395 --> 44:10.022
This will go muchfaster with two people.

44:10.064 --> 44:12.358
- Is that the--- Folding kayak.

44:12.358 --> 44:15.152
Prototype from Oregon,lighter material.

44:15.194 --> 44:16.028
Come on.

44:18.906 --> 44:20.032
So what brings you by?

44:20.074 --> 44:21.700
- Well, I've been doingsome more research

44:21.742 --> 44:23.702
on the Arizonadistribution facility.

44:23.744 --> 44:25.245
- Pop that into place, there.

44:26.497 --> 44:28.248
- Thinking longterm, itoccurs to me we'll probably

44:28.290 --> 44:31.001
need a second onewithin a couple years.

44:31.043 --> 44:32.836
- Tighten your bow strap.

44:32.878 --> 44:34.046
Second one, what?

44:34.088 --> 44:35.798
- Second distribution facility.

44:35.839 --> 44:40.886
So the way I'm figuring is,why not secure that second site

44:40.928 --> 44:42.888
right now, while we'realready thinking about

44:42.888 --> 44:44.014
what we really need?

44:45.099 --> 44:46.225
- And you're bow faring.

44:47.226 --> 44:49.019
- This time we buildit from scratch,

44:49.061 --> 44:51.397
we build it to ourown specifications,

44:51.397 --> 44:52.940
like we've always talked about.

44:52.981 --> 44:55.192
- You have a place in mind?- I do.

44:56.026 --> 44:58.779
Harmony Ranch, North Dakota.

45:02.574 --> 45:05.202
(soft music)

45:10.290 --> 45:14.253
(Jill and Michael chattering)

45:27.724 --> 45:30.269
(upbeat music)

45:40.446 --> 45:41.530
- Hey.- Oh!

45:41.572 --> 45:43.198
- Sorry, didn'tmean to disturb you.

45:43.240 --> 45:44.283
- Oh, no, it's okay.

45:44.366 --> 45:45.242
Taylor told me aboutthis place earlier,

45:45.284 --> 45:46.326
so I wanted to check it out.

45:47.244 --> 45:49.538
So all of this is Harmony?

45:51.457 --> 45:52.207
- Mostly.

45:52.249 --> 45:55.002
But also in echoes.

45:56.295 --> 45:57.588
(laughing)

45:57.629 --> 45:59.381
Yeah, that's Hank Ketchum.

45:59.423 --> 46:00.466
He founded the ranch.

46:00.507 --> 46:02.468
- And had a flair for fashion.

46:02.509 --> 46:03.719
- [Josh] Yes, he did.

46:04.678 --> 46:06.388
- How long has the ranchbeen in your family?

46:06.430 --> 46:08.474
- Four generations.

46:08.474 --> 46:10.058
Hoping there'll be a fifth.

46:12.102 --> 46:14.563
- Did you know how muchtrouble the ranch was in?

46:16.148 --> 46:17.149
- No.

46:17.191 --> 46:19.318
No, dad was incharge, and I was away

46:19.318 --> 46:22.029
at grad schooluntil six years ago.

46:22.988 --> 46:24.615
- Where'd you go?- Cornell.

46:25.699 --> 46:26.909
MS in Animal Science.

46:27.034 --> 46:29.244
And it's also where I ranacross a little coffee shop

46:29.286 --> 46:30.496
called Aunt Mary's Coffee,

46:30.496 --> 46:32.289
and I still get the beansfrom there to this day.

46:32.331 --> 46:34.500
- I fully support thatextravagant decision.

46:34.500 --> 46:35.667
- Yeah, thank you.

46:35.667 --> 46:38.337
And by the way, love the outfit.

46:38.378 --> 46:39.254
- Thank you.

46:40.255 --> 46:41.381
I'm aware that it'sfunny that I work

46:41.423 --> 46:42.841
for an outdooradventure gear company

46:42.883 --> 46:45.177
and I had to getmy ranch wardrobe

46:45.177 --> 46:47.387
at a local general store, but.

46:47.429 --> 46:49.014
- I see you kept the boots.

46:49.014 --> 46:52.184
- Well, they're worn in.- Uh huh.

46:52.226 --> 46:53.852
- It's more comfortable.

46:53.894 --> 46:57.022
- Or you just like them.- Possibly.

46:57.022 --> 46:58.190
(laughing)

46:58.232 --> 46:59.399
But if asked about itoutside these four walls,

46:59.441 --> 47:01.568
I'm gonna deny it.- Okay.

47:01.610 --> 47:02.861
That'll be our secret.

47:05.364 --> 47:07.491
(laughing)

47:09.117 --> 47:10.869
(soft music)

47:10.911 --> 47:12.955
- [Alex] So what's theCentennial gonna be like?

47:12.996 --> 47:15.582
- Well, this is normally whenwe have our fall celebration,

47:15.624 --> 47:17.459
so Centennial willjust take its spot.

47:17.501 --> 47:20.045
- Oh.- But we'll do some fun stuff.

47:20.087 --> 47:24.049
Music, games.- That does sound fun.

47:24.049 --> 47:26.885
- Yeah, Taylor's gonnabake about 1,000 pies.

47:26.885 --> 47:28.178
- Oh, having just goneshopping with her,

47:28.220 --> 47:30.389
yes, she is.(laughing)

47:30.430 --> 47:31.515
- What are you gonna do

47:31.557 --> 47:33.725
to celebrate thehistory of the place?

47:33.767 --> 47:36.311
- You know, you're justgonna have to wait and see.

47:36.353 --> 47:37.479
- Mysterious.

47:38.230 --> 47:39.565
- So I have to know,after your first,

47:39.565 --> 47:42.109
full day as a rancheris coming to a close,

47:42.150 --> 47:44.736
what do you think?- I had such a wonderful time.

47:44.778 --> 47:47.072
I loved being able toride again, thank you.

47:47.114 --> 47:48.073
- You're welcome.

47:49.074 --> 47:50.742
And also no prep workfor you for tomorrow,

47:50.784 --> 47:53.203
so feel free to sleep in.- Thank you.

47:53.245 --> 47:55.455
- I'll come findyou around noon.

47:57.082 --> 47:58.333
- Noon it is.- Okay.

47:59.126 --> 48:02.087
Well, have a goodnight, Ms. McKenna.

48:03.422 --> 48:04.506
- Night.

48:20.606 --> 48:23.191
(soft music)

48:25.360 --> 48:28.113
(hoses snorting)

48:32.284 --> 48:33.285
(laughing)

48:33.327 --> 48:34.494
- Nice!

48:34.536 --> 48:35.996
- I am loving this trip.

48:36.038 --> 48:39.291
- Does a certain Michael Getzhave anything to do with that?

48:39.333 --> 48:42.377
- He's not hurtingthe experience.

48:42.419 --> 48:44.129
(loud crunching)- Oh.

48:45.589 --> 48:47.799
So, was yesterday a date?

48:48.800 --> 48:50.218
- I can't quite tell.

48:50.260 --> 48:51.970
You know how long it'sbeen since I've had

48:52.012 --> 48:53.388
to read dating signals?

48:54.348 --> 48:56.934
Men are so complicated.

48:57.726 --> 48:59.061
(loud crunching)

48:59.102 --> 49:02.814
Still, it's kinda nice toeven be having the discussion.

49:05.275 --> 49:06.485
What about you?

49:07.569 --> 49:10.447
(loud crunching)

49:10.489 --> 49:11.490
- What about me?

49:11.490 --> 49:13.450
- Can you have the discussion?

49:14.409 --> 49:18.497
- Oh no, there is nodiscussion to be had.

49:19.289 --> 49:21.124
- Really?- Mm-hmm.

49:21.166 --> 49:25.379
- Because you were spendingan awful lot of time with him.

49:25.420 --> 49:27.297
(loud crunching)

49:27.339 --> 49:30.175
- He's just showingme the ranch.

49:30.175 --> 49:31.927
You know, in caseGreat Frontiers wants

49:31.969 --> 49:35.013
to invest or something.- Invest, really?

49:35.847 --> 49:37.516
That'd be good.- Yeah.

